org.springdata.cassandra.cql.option
Enum TableOption

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<TableOption>
      org.springdata.cassandra.cql.option.TableOption
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<TableOption>, Option
public enum TableOption
extends Enum<TableOption>
implements Option

Enumeration that represents all known table options. If a table option is not listed here, but is supported by Cassandra, use the method WithOptionsSpecification.with(String, Object, boolean, boolean) to write the raw value. Implements TableOption.CachingOption via delegation, since Enums can't extend anything.

Author:
Matthew T. Adams
See Also:
TableOption.CompactionOption, TableOption.CompressionOption, TableOption.CachingOption

toString

public String toString(Object value)
Description copied from interface: Option
First ensures that the given value is coerceable into the type expected by this option, then returns the result of Object.toString() called on the given value. If this option is escaping quotes (Option.escapesValue() is true), then single quotes will be escaped, and if this option is quoting values ( Option.quotesValue() is true), then the value will be surrounded by single quotes. Given null, returns null.

Specified by:
toString in interface Option
See Also:
Option.escapesValue(), Option.quotesValue()
